The workflow for unsupervised discovery of I2-II-IV-X4 chalcogenides for thin-film PVs is illustrated in Fig. 1, including four modules: determination of crystal structures (Fig. 1a–d)38, element selection from the periodic table (Fig. 1e), the establishment of the ML model (Fig. 1f), and ab initio calculation (Fig. 1g). In this procedure, considering that the I2-II-IV-X4 chalcogenide has four different space groups, I222, P31, Ama2, and I4¯2m\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
